dcterms:description: A learning and evaluation environment for Neural Motion Planning (NMP) algorithms, focused on robotic manipulators, providing baseline implementations for learning control policies and a simulator based on PyBullet.
dcterms:title: RoboArm-NMP

dcterms:creator: Constantinos Chamzas
Carlos Quintero-Pena
Zachary Kingston
Andreas Orthey
Daniel Rakita
Michael Gleicher
Marc Toussaint
Lydia E Kavraki
dcterms:description: Tasks generated for benchmarking motion planning datasets, providing a set of test cases for evaluating NMP algorithms.
dcterms:title: Chamzas et al. (2021) tasks

dcterms:description: Trajectories generated using sampling-based motion planning methods, used for training and evaluating NMP algorithms.
dcterms:title: SBMP (Sampling-Based Motion Planning) trajectories

dcterms:description: Tasks created within the RoboArm-NMP environment, categorized by difficulty levels (easy, medium, hard) based on random box configurations.
dcterms:title: Random boxes tasks (easy, medium, hard)

dcterms:description: Specific tasks defined in the context of the RoboArm-NMP environment that test generalization capabilities to unseen obstacle configurations.
dcterms:title: OOD (Out-of-Distribution) tasks

dcterms:description: Point cloud and image datasets collected from the environment, used for training encoders in the RoboArm-NMP.
dcterms:title: PointCloud and Image datasets used for training encoders
